  • Classes in io.prometheus.client.metrics used by io.prometheus.client.metrics 
    Class and Description
    Counter
    Counter is a Metric that tracks the addition or subtraction of a value from itself.
    Counter.Builder
    Define the characteristics for this Counter.
    Counter.Child
    A concrete instance of Counter for a unique set of label dimensions.
    Counter.Partial
    A derivative of Counter that lets you accumulate labels to build a concrete metric via Counter.Partial.apply() for mutation with the methods of Counter.Child.
    Gauge
    Gauge is a Metric that reports instantaneous values based on external state.
    Gauge.Builder
    Define the characteristics for this Gauge.
    Gauge.Child
    A concrete instance of Gauge for a unique set of label dimensions.
    Gauge.Partial
    A derivative of Gauge that lets you accumulate labels to build a concrete metric via Gauge.Partial.apply() for mutation with the methods of Gauge.Child.
    Metric
    A Metric is the base type of all Prometheus metrics.
    Metric.Builder
    A Metric.Builder is used to create a Metric's descriptor, which describes everything about the metric: name, required label dimensions (i.e., metric cardinality), docstring, etc.
    Metric.Child
    Metric.Child is a concrete metric, the thing you mutate.
    Metric.Partial
    Metric.Partial is an incomplete incarnation of a Metric.Child that you add label value pair to with Metric.Partial.labelPair(String, String).
    Summary
    Summary is a Metric that samples events over sliding windows of time.
    Summary.Builder 
    Summary.Child
    A concrete instance of Summary for a unique set of label dimensions.
    Summary.Partial
    A derivative of Summary that lets you accumulate labels to build a concrete metric via Summary.Partial.apply() for mutation with the methods of Summary.Child.
